Start by calculating the initial terms of the sequence:
\begin{align*}
u_2 &= \frac{1}{2 - b}, \\
u_3 &= \frac{1}{2 - \frac{1}{2 - b}} = \frac{2 - b}{2b - 1}, \\
u_4 &= \frac{1}{2 - \frac{2 - b}{2b - 1}} = \frac{2b - 1}{4b - 3}.
\end{align*}

We continue this process to search for a cycle:
\begin{align*}
u_5 &= \frac{1}{2 - \frac{2b - 1}{4b - 3}} = \frac{4b - 3}{6b - 5}, \\
u_6 &= \frac{1}{2 - \frac{4b - 3}{6b - 5}} = b.
\end{align*}

Since $u_6 = u_1 = b$, the sequence is periodic with a period of 5.

Therefore, $u_{10} = u_5 = \boxed{\frac{4b - 3}{6b - 5}}$.

