\end{cases}
\end{aligned}
$$
yields \( x_4 = \frac{6+3a}{4} \).
In this case, \( 1  \frac{10 + 4\sqrt{7}}{3} \) (the case \( a  4 \) and \( a > \frac{10 + 4\sqrt{7}}{3} \), \( m = -\frac{3a^2 - 20a + 12}{16} \) satisfies the condition. \(\boxed{m = -\frac{3a^2 - 20a + 12}{16}}\)

