Since the smaller circles touch the larger circle and each other at the center, the diameter of each smaller circle is equal to the radius of the larger circle, which is \( 8 \). Therefore, the radius of each smaller circle is \( 4 \).

The area of the larger circle is \( \pi \times 8^2 = 64\pi \).
The area of each smaller circle is \( \pi \times 4^2 = 16\pi \).

The area of the shaded region is:
\[ 64\pi - 2 \times 16\pi = 64\pi - 32\pi = \boxed{32\pi}. \]

